Ambroveneto's purchase may mark the first step towards taking full control
of the bank. Among other shareholders in ISA are Banca San Paolo di Brescia
and Mittel, two financial institutions largely controlled by Ambroveneto's
chairman, Mr Giovanni Bazoli.
