FT  30 JAN 92 / UK Company News: Margins expand as Adscene hits Pounds 0.7m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pre-tax profits at Adscene Group recovered strongly in the six months to
November 30, and shareholders benefit by having their interim dividend
doubled to 1.5p.
The group, which publishes 33 local newspaper titles in Kent, Lincolnshire
and London, saw profits rise from Pounds 462,000 to Pounds 720,000 largely
as a result of a lower cost base.
Mr Harry Lambert, chairman, said margins expanded 3 per cent to 12.6 per
