the sale of the Lincoln property for Pounds 1.2m.
Turnover fell to Pounds 8.1m (Pounds 9.2m). In Kent the group lifted
publishing turnover by 13 per cent. In Lincolnshire and London advertising
revenue continued to fall but there were some signs recently that the
decline had slowed.
The printing division's turnover again reduced by 23 per cent but margins
were still above 10 per cent. There were only limited opportunities in the
immediate future for new printing contracts, Mr Lambert stressed.
Earnings per share rose to 3.01p (1.78p).
